OL,4,
OL,5,COutlook for Sun 29 Mar to Tue 7 AprFA
OL,6,Fbroadly changeable pattern will
OL,7,Fcontinue, at least through the first
OL,8,Fpart of this period, as further
OL,9,Ffrontal systems move across parts of
OL,10,Fthe UK, bringing rain and stronger
OL,11,Fwinds at times. Weather fronts are
OL,12,Flikely to be more active across
OL,13,Fnorthern areas, meaning the wettest
OL,14,Fand windiest conditions are more
OL,15,Flikely here. As they come south, often
OL,16,Frunning in to a ridge of higher
OL,17,Fpressure extending from the southwest,
OL,18,Ffronts will generally weaken and
OL,19,Frainfall amounts will be smaller. This
OL,20,Farea of high pressure is likely to
OL,21,Fbecome increasingly dominant through
OL,22,Fthe period, with more settled
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,23,Fconditions perhaps becoming more
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
OL,24,Fprevalent across the UK. In this
OL,25,Fsetup, temperatures will probably pan
OL,26,Fout close to average overall, with
